  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "buSKsrznGOCad2OuaZfMv4AzcjI=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\n\nThe Bee Reactor Adapter performs **app-layer AES-256-GCM encryption before upload** rather than relying on Swarm-native encryption, to control keys and keep references 32 bytes.\n\n## Evidence\n\nKey derivation chain:\n```\nwallet.personal_sign(msg) -> keccak256 -> secp256k1 private key\n  -> SHA-256 -> AES-256 symmetric key\n```\n\nCiphertext format:\n```\n[SWE prefix (3 bytes)] [IV (12 bytes)] [ciphertext + GCM auth tag]\n```\n\nAdvantages over Swarm-native (`Swarm-Encrypt: true`):\n- Full control over key management\n- Reference stays 32 bytes (no embedded 32-byte decryption key)\n- Compatible with any storage backend, not just Swarm\n- Deterministic: same wallet = same key on any device\n\nSharing today uses `SHA-256(sender_address:recipient_address)` \u2014 both parties derive the same key independently (but this is non-revocable; ACT is the planned replacement).\n\n## Why it matters\n\nApp-layer encryption decouples the document-level security story from the Swarm transport. The deterministic wallet-derived key enables cross-device recovery without any server-side key escrow.\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:45.000Z"
    }
  },
